    "content": "## Basic\nThe basic color picker allows users to select a color.\n<How className='min-w-40' toUse=\"colors/color-picker/color-picker-demo\" />\n\n## Installation\n<Installation options={{isComponent: true}} items={['color-picker']}/>\n\n## Composed Components\n<Composed components={['color-area', 'color-field', 'color-slider', 'color-swatch', 'field', 'popover']}/>\n\n## Manual Installation\n<Installation options={{isManual: true}} items={['react-aria-components', 'justd-icons']}/>\n<SourceCode toShow={['color-picker']}/>\n\n## Anatomy\n<Anatomy show='color-picker-anatomy'/>\n\n## Enable Format Selection\nEnable users to select the format of the color value (e.g., RGB, HSL).\n<How className='min-w-40' toUse=\"colors/color-picker/color-picker-enable-selection-format-demo\" />\n\n## Combination\nCombine both swatch and selection format options in the color picker.\n<How className='min-w-40' toUse=\"colors/color-picker/color-picker-combination-demo\" />\n\n## Label\nAdd a label to the color picker for better accessibility and user guidance.\n<How className='min-w-40' toUse=\"colors/color-picker/color-picker-with-label-demo\" />\n\n## Dynamic Label\nDynamically update the label based on the selected color.\n```\nimport { ColorPicker, defaultColor } from \"ui\"\n\nconst [color, setColor] = React.useState(defaultColor)\nreturn <ColorPicker label={color.toString('hex')} value={color} onChange={setColor} />\n```\n\n## Description\nInclude a description to provide additional information or instructions.\n<How className='min-w-40' toUse=\"colors/color-picker/color-picker-with-description-demo\" />\n\n## Controlled\nControl the selected color with the `value` prop to sync it with your application's state.\n<How className='min-w-40' toUse=\"colors/color-picker/color-picker-controlled-demo\" />\n\n## Disabled\nDisable the color picker by setting the `isDisabled` prop, making it non-interactive.\n<How className='min-w-40' toUse=\"colors/color-picker/color-picker-disabled-demo\" />",
