    "content": "## Basic\n\nA textarea is a larger box where you can type in text, like your name, email, or a longer message.\n<How minW72 toUse=\"forms/textarea/textarea-demo\" />\n\n## Installation\n<Installation options={{ isComponent: true }} items={['textarea']}/>\n\n## Composed Components\n<Composed components={['field']}/>\n\n## Manual Installation\n<Installation options={{ isManual: true }} items={['react-aria-components']}/>\n\n<SourceCode toShow={['textarea']}/>\n\n## Anatomy\n<Anatomy show='textarea-anatomy'/>\n\n## Description\nYou can add a description to the textarea by using the `description` prop.\n<How minW72 toUse=\"forms/textarea/textarea-description-demo\" />\n\n\n## Controlled\nYou can control the textarea value by using the `value` prop.\n<How minW72 toUse=\"forms/textarea/textarea-controlled-demo\" />\n\n## Uncontrolled\nYou can control the textarea value by using the `defaultValue` prop.\n<How minW72 toUse=\"forms/textarea/textarea-uncontrolled-demo\" />\n\n## Validation\nTry submitting the form without filling it out to see the error state in action.\n<How minW72 toUse=\"forms/textarea/textarea-validation-demo\" />\n\n## Readonly\nWhen the textarea is set to readonly, it cannot be edited.\n<How minW72 toUse=\"forms/textarea/textarea-readonly-demo\" />\n\n## Disabled\nWhen the textarea is disabled, it becomes non-editable and appears inactive.\n<How minW72 toUse=\"forms/textarea/textarea-disabled-demo\" />",
